HEADWORD: Neurasthenia
<hw>Neu*ras`the*ni"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>ney^ron</grk> nerve + <?/ weakness.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A condition of nervous debility supposed to be dependent upon
impairment in the functions of the spinal cord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

